The chance that a snake will bite you is not too high, with regular contact, it is afraid of itself.
And if she has room for it, she likes to crawl away with a loud hiss.
It will only attack if it feels very threatened - for example, if you accidentally step on it.
Even its bite is not a tragedy, its poison is very effective against small mammals, but it does not kill people.
